name: SeaFlower
description:
ABOUT THE HOME ENERGY RATING SCALE
The HERS (Home Energy Rating System) Index allows buyers to compare the relative energy efficiency of different homes. The HERS Index home energy rating is determined by an independent RESNET-certified home energy rater ("Rater"). The lower a home’s score, the more energy efficient it is in comparison to the HERS referenced home. For every one-point decrease in the HERS Index score, there is a corresponding one percent (1%) reduction in energy consumption as compared to a home with a HERS Index of 100. A home with a HERS score of 100 reflects a home built to 2006 IEEC Building Codes. See the bottom of this page for more information on HERS scores.

amenities.name: Within master
amenities.description: Within the master planned community of SeaFlower

amenities.name: Situated 1,175
amenities.description: Situated on 1,175 acres of land that once served as a family flower farm, SeaFlower is coming to life and redefining coastal living

amenities.name: future front
amenities.description: 105 future front doors

amenities.name: Single-family home
amenities.description: Single-family home designs with both front and alley-load homes

amenities.name: Ideally located
amenities.description: Ideally located in southwest Bradenton, FL

amenities.name: -acre lake
amenities.description: 19-acre lake and surrounding lakefront park at the center of the community, picture picnics along the lake or stargazing after sunset

amenities.name: wide, multi-modal
amenities.description: A wide, multi-modal trail weaves throughout SeaFlower and connects to the SeaFlower Village Center, amenities, pocket parks, lakes, and natural areas, as well as with the surrounding community

amenities.name: Stories
amenities.description: Amenity Center affectionately named "The Garden Club" inspired by the history of the land

amenities.name: Garden Club
amenities.description: The Garden Club amenity center will feature a resort-style pool and lap lanes, residents club, state-of-the-art fitness center, meeting hall, 4 pickleball courts, and so much more

amenities.name: Enjoy great
amenities.description: Enjoy the great outdoors with amenities like the event lawn, amphitheater, and play area

amenities.name: Room for
amenities.description: Room for our furry-friends at with 2 community dog parks

amenities.name: Smart home
amenities.description: Smart home technology to make your home as smart as you want it

amenities.name: Florida Green
amenities.description: Florida Green Building Coalition (FGBC) 2023 Builder of the Year for the most certified single-family homes

amenities.name: Bradenton area
amenities.description: The Bradenton area offers the School Choice Program so families have access to a variety of school in the area including public and private

amenities.name: SeaFlower Village
amenities.description: SeaFlower Village Center, evoking the nostalgia of a quaint town Main Street where you will find a Publix, a mix of retail shops, restaurants and the Village Green providing multiple ways to gather and have fun

amenities.name: surrounding area
amenities.description: In the surrounding area there is an array of mom and pop shops and restaurants for our residents to explore

amenities.name: Soak sun
amenities.description: Soak up the sun with your toes in the sand with sugar sand beaches less than 3 miles away

amenities.name: Anna Maria
amenities.description: Anna Maria Island is just over 3 miles away, as well a nearby Longboat Key, St. Armand’s Circle, and neighboring barrier islands

amenities.name: Only miles
amenities.description: Only 3 miles away from IMG Academy the world’s leading sports education brand, providing access and opportunity for student-athletes through innovative on-campus and online programming and experiences

amenities.name: Catch baseball
amenities.description: Catch a baseball game at LECOM Park where spring training is held for the Pittsburgh Pirates, 6 miles away, or watch the Bradenton Marauders during the season

amenities.name: Stroll Bradenton
amenities.description: Stroll the Bradenton Riverwalk, only 7.5 miles away. Here you'll discover a scenic 1.5-mile waterfront park featuring a skatepark, splash pad, playgrounds, and the Mosaic Amphitheater for live events. It's a perfect spot for a leisurely stroll or family outing

amenities.name: Get touch
amenities.description: Get in touch with nature by visiting the Robinson Preserve (6 miles) or De Soto National Memorial Park (5 miles). Both offer acres of natural habitat, miles of trails, birdwatching and so much more

amenities.name: museums are
amenities.description: If museums are your thing you are in luck! The Bishop Museum of Science and Nature and the Florida Maritime Museum are nearby and provide engaging exhibits and community events
